Contenders to Christ's throne.

33:18.706 --> 33:21.834
Our job is to rid the world
of their competing narratives.

33:22.418 --> 33:27.090
Charlemagne, Lincoln, Belushi, you name it.

33:28.549 --> 33:32.345
You will be my right-hand man.

33:35.765 --> 33:39.060
- The Grail killed Abraham Lincoln?
- Mmm.

33:39.477 --> 33:40.895
Yes, we did.

33:41.938 --> 33:43.815
And why did we do that?

33:44.565 --> 33:46.275
He preserved the union,

33:47.276 --> 33:50.822
won the war, sense of humor.

33:51.114 --> 33:53.658
His polling was probably through the roof.

33:55.576 --> 33:56.703
Something tells me

33:56.786 --> 34:00.123
you're going to do
great things here, <i>Herr</i> Starr.

34:02.959 --> 34:06.379
Thank you for this opportunity.

34:55.261 --> 34:58.431
Blood, people! Blood and brains!

34:58.514 --> 35:01.893
And people screaming until their lungs hurt!

35:01.976 --> 35:05.688
That's how bad it's gonna be.
That is what's comin'!

35:07.190 --> 35:09.317
So, watch your asses.

35:09.400 --> 35:12.278
I'm takin' five. Don't forget the beer bucket.

35:17.867 --> 35:21.162
Ah, Father, I noticed you standing there.

35:22.455 --> 35:25.458
Always good to see
a fellow soldier for the Lord.

35:27.126 --> 35:28.252
Question for you.

35:28.336 --> 35:29.378
Hit me.

35:32.381 --> 35:34.717
Are you crazy or just a con man?

35:35.843 --> 35:37.303
Are those my only two choices?

35:37.386 --> 35:39.597
'Cause I normally describe myself

35:39.680 --> 35:43.851
as a left-handed,
alcoholic, sinner child of God.

35:47.063 --> 35:48.397
I don't mean to insult you.

35:48.981 --> 35:52.735
It's just... I've been wondering
about the end of the world.

35:55.238 --> 35:56.572
Well...

35:58.199 --> 36:00.201
Buy me a beer. We'll wonder together.

36:01.244 --> 36:03.538
Sorry again about the confusion.

36:03.621 --> 36:06.916
Ever since the carts
started operating in tandem,

36:06.999 --> 36:09.335
- you'd be surprised how much this happens.
- Mmm-hmm.

36:09.627 --> 36:10.795
I'm used to it.

36:10.878 --> 36:13.923
Alcohol and a lack of vital signs
will do it to you every time.

36:20.096 --> 36:21.097
Oh...

36:22.640 --> 36:23.850
Poor people.

36:25.268 --> 36:28.396
I'd rather be them than him.

36:32.149 --> 36:33.442
Yeah.

37:05.057 --> 37:08.644
Ten, nine, eight, seven,

37:08.728 --> 37:10.062
six, five, four...

37:26.203 --> 37:29.832
I'm real sorry about your boyfriend, ma'am.
Terrible loss.

37:32.501 --> 37:34.045
Y'all should be sorry.

37:36.130 --> 37:38.633
We robbed you assholes blind.

37:39.800 --> 37:43.137
That wasn't my boyfriend,
and he wasn't dead.

37:44.931 --> 37:49.018
We came in here,
played y'all for the idiots y'all are,

37:50.186 --> 37:52.521
took your money, and drank your beer.

37:53.272 --> 37:55.816
So, put your goddamn hats back on.

37:56.817 --> 38:01.489
And tell me which one of you
banjo diddlin' little bitches

38:01.572 --> 38:05.534
has got the balls to earn your money back?

38:38.401 --> 38:42.238
Ten, nine, eight, seven,

38:42.321 --> 38:45.032
six, five, four...

38:53.958 --> 38:55.209
Again.

39:02.925 --> 39:06.595
So, the world's ending, huh?

39:06.929 --> 39:07.930
Mmm-hmm.

39:09.932 --> 39:11.017
Why?

39:11.809 --> 39:13.477
What makes you say that?

39:15.271 --> 39:16.731
Common sense.

39:16.814 --> 39:18.524
Science.

39:18.607 --> 39:20.526
The world's been ending since it started.

39:21.235 --> 39:22.653
That's not an answer.

39:23.112 --> 39:24.447
What's the question?

39:25.865 --> 39:28.284
What are you looking for? Proof?

39:28.951 --> 39:30.828
Well, that's what
you're advertising here, right?

39:30.911 --> 39:32.997
Signs of the apocalypse and all that.

39:33.122 --> 39:35.082
Ah...

39:36.584 --> 39:38.711
That's mostly just metaphor.

39:40.796 --> 39:44.300
I hear things, I see things.

39:45.342 --> 39:49.805
People come up to me,
they say all sorts of crazy stuff.

39:50.556 --> 39:53.517
And there has been an uptake
ever since Tom Cruise exploded.

39:53.601 --> 39:54.977
No question.

39:56.979 --> 39:58.773
The Cubs winning. Trump.

40:01.484 --> 40:02.735
This flying pig.

40:02.818 --> 40:05.237
That's real Wrath of God stuff, right?

40:06.864 --> 40:09.950
But sooner or later,
there's always an explanation.

40:11.243 --> 40:12.620
Strong pitchin',

40:13.662 --> 40:15.706
KGB interference, whatever.

40:18.292 --> 40:21.837
In the end, there's always a good reason.

40:23.422 --> 40:27.426
So, you're just out here
scarin' people. For money.

40:27.510 --> 40:29.136
They are already scared.

40:29.762 --> 40:32.264
They come listen to me
talk about the end of the world,

40:32.348 --> 40:35.267
so they can worry about that
instead of what really scares 'em.

40:35.684 --> 40:37.061
Which is what?

40:39.688 --> 40:40.898
Themselves.

40:43.109 --> 40:47.696
What is more frightening
than who we are and what we done?

40:52.034 --> 40:55.788
Well, I have got car payments,
and a drinking problem.

40:55.871 --> 40:57.873
So, I should probably get back to it.

40:58.833 --> 40:59.875
Hey.

41:03.129 --> 41:07.258
You hear about this whole
fractional soul-selling thing?

41:08.217 --> 41:09.385
The Japanese, sure.

41:09.635 --> 41:12.930
This parishioner came to me about it.

41:15.391 --> 41:18.477
Just thinkin' about
selling a small amount of his, you know?

41:18.561 --> 41:20.646
Of course I said, "No way."

41:21.730 --> 41:23.899
This guy was in quite a tough situation,

41:24.817 --> 41:26.861
friends were in trouble, needed help.

41:27.486 --> 41:30.865
So, by selling off this small part of his soul,

41:30.948 --> 41:34.910
and I mean, just tiny, like, 1%.

41:37.246 --> 41:42.835
I thought, maybe it was a sacrifice
worth making, you know?

41:49.592 --> 41:54.430
I would tell your parishioner
that if he wants to help his friends,

41:55.306 --> 41:57.141
he should give a kidney.

42:04.315 --> 42:07.193
And if you're looking
for signs of the apocalypse,

42:08.068 --> 42:11.488
I would start with men selling off their souls.

42:31.467 --> 42:33.594
The situation has been handled.

42:35.721 --> 42:36.972
Where to next?

42:37.056 --> 42:38.641
<i>New Orleans, sir.</i>

42:38.724 --> 42:40.392
And the target?

42:40.476 --> 42:43.062
<i>A preacher, Jesse Custer.</i>

42:43.145 --> 42:44.772
I'm on my way.

43:09.713 --> 43:12.508
<i>The water was highly toxic.</i>

43:12.591 --> 43:15.594
<i>I'm sorry,
but would you mind explaining it again?</i>

43:15.678 --> 43:19.932
<i>The water killed
the whole village, made the pig float.</i>

43:20.474 --> 43:22.685
<i>The water made the pig float?</i>

43:23.602 --> 43:27.731
<i>How could contaminated water
produce such an unusual effect?</i>

43:28.315 --> 43:31.193
<i>It was saturated
with hydrogen atoms,</i>

43:31.277 --> 43:33.362
<i>permeated the pig's tissue,</i>

43:33.445 --> 43:37.658
<i>resulted in limited levitation,
like a meat balloon.</i>

43:37.741 --> 43:38.867
<i>Meat balloon?</i>

43:38.951 --> 43:40.286
<i>Meat balloon.</i>

43:40.369 --> 43:42.454
<i>It just seems so incredible...</i>

43:42.538 --> 43:44.999
<i>Remind me. Are you a scientist?</i>

43:45.666 --> 43:46.709
<i>No.</i>

43:47.501 --> 43:49.211
<i>Well, then shut up.</i>
